<p>The advice to "save for retirement" typically includes the assumption that "retirement" means you work until age 65, at which point you stop working and enjoy your golden years. Maybe that's exactly what you want. Maybe not. But it's important to recognize that the traditional view of retirement is NOT the only option available to you.
